rComments: Not too hard and you can do good if you put in effort. 50% of your grade (include final) is based on bellringer and identify keying, its a practical course so be prepared. Utilize the lab time, practice keying as much as you can.

When he said no calculations would be tested, he actually meant beside all those calculations he showed you, no other calculations would be tested. Tough tests, extremely short test time. His lectures were fine and well explained, but yeah other peoples comments were true, he was not that patient to questions.

WORSE CLASS EVER! he so did not respect anyone, he kicks out students when they approach him during office hours he reads from the book, everything is from the book you can read at home but tests are TOUGH!! very hard marker, doesn't care, doesn't allow remark, nor allow discussion. he will make you feel STUPID!
